The Hunger Level Tracker is a lightweight web application built with Flask that simulates and manages
a user’s hunger level as a dynamic, time-dependent state. 
The system models hunger on a scale from 0 to 100,
where it gradually increases based on elapsed time and can be reduced through user actions such as eating. 
By combining simple backend logic with an interactive interface, 
the app demonstrates key software engineering concepts including state management,
time-based computation, and client-server interaction, 
making it a practical foundation for more advanced applications such as health monitoring systems, 
behavioral simulations, or data-driven predictive models.